You can see BBCodes here.<br />Quoting and outputting fixed-width text.<br /><br /><blockquote><div><cite>Mr. Blobby wrote:</cite><br />The text Mr. Blobby wrote would go here.<br /></div></blockquote><blockquote><div><cite>Mr. Blobby wrote:</cite><br />The text Mr. Blobby wrote would go here.<blockquote><div><cite>Mr. Blobby wrote:</cite>The text Mr. Blobby wrote would go here<br /></div></blockquote></div></blockquote><blockquote><div><cite>Mr. Blobby wrote:</cite><br />The text Mr. Blobby wrote would go here.<blockquote><div><cite>Mr. Blobby wrote:</cite>The text Mr. Blobby wrote would go here.<blockquote><div><cite>Mr. Blobby wrote:</cite>The text Mr. Blobby wrote would go here.<br /></div></blockquote></div></blockquote></div></blockquote><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />The text somebody wrote would go here.<br /></div></blockquote><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />The text somebody wrote would go here.<blockquote class="uncited"><div>The text somebody wrote would go here.<br /></div></blockquote></div></blockquote><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />The text somebody wrote would go here.<blockquote class="uncited"><div>The text somebody wrote would go here.<blockquote class="uncited"><div>The text somebody wrote would go here.<br /></div></blockquote></div></blockquote></div></blockquote><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><code>echo &quot;This is some code&quot;; </code></div><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><code>&lt;?php define('IN_PHPBB', true);<br />$phpbb_root_path = (defined('PHPBB_ROOT_PATH')) ? PHPBB_ROOT_PATH : './';<br />$phpEx = substr(strrchr(__FILE__, '.'), 1);<br />include($phpbb_root_path . 'common.' . $phpEx);<br />include($phpbb_root_path . 'includes/functions_display.' . $phpEx);</code></div><hr />
]]></content>
